The ruling party started the hashtag #WeAreANC to connect with their supporters but tweeps criticised the party instead. CAPE TOWN - A call by the African National Congress (ANC) to their supporters to share pictures or short video clips of how they are promoting Unity in Action in their areas took an unexpected turn when Twitter followers instead attacked the party.The ruling party started the hashtag #WeAreANC to connect with their supporters ahead of their 105th anniversary celebration on 8 January.The ANC will celebrate the anniversary in Orlando Stadium, Soweto under the theme Unity in Action .Below are some of the tweets that were posted. Ouch! Talk about unintended consequences.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)